(1, '1', 'How much do we know about counterfeit products in tech market?', 'counterfeit products in tech market', NULL, '<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: 150%; text-align: left;\" align=\"center\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 16.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 11.0pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\">How much do we know about counterfeit products in tech market?</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: 150%;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\">Have you ever purchased an iPhone 12 Pro Max at 12,500 BDT? Or have you ever purchased an iPhone at common market price, but the appearance and quality of the phone did not seem up to the mark? Yes, today we are going to talk about the so-called counterfeit tech gadgets that have flooded the market of Bangladesh.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: 150%;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\">Look closely at the picture of the two iPhone. Can you guess which one is real and which one is fake? Should we worry about choosing the right one or should we question how can counterfeit product of iPhone brand even exist in the market? Scary right? What if you end up buying a fake one with the same amount of the original one? </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: 150%;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\">To avoid such financial tragedy, we have to be aware about the tech market not just in Bangladesh but also around the world, as well as educate ourselves on certain factors. The OECD reckon that in 2017, 20% of all mobile phones shipped internationally were fake. In 2012, a UAE telecoms operator banned over 18,000 devices from their network, citing fire hazards and leaking batteries. In Uganda, 9 million phones were disabled in 2018, and it\'s estimated that 40% of all active phones in the country were fake prior to this action <span style=\"mso-no-proof: yes;\">(Device Atlas, 2019)</span>.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: 150%;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\">So why does a counterfeit gadget come at such a cheap rate? Bad quality! It is as simple as that. These items lack a lot of features of the original ones and materials used for making these are also cheap. This leads to the creation of certain risk factors that comes with purchasing these phones. What are they?</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: 150%;\"><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\">Malware:</span></strong><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\"> Dodgy devices, once activated, can download malware that propagates throughout the network it connects to (and infect other devices on the network) <span style=\"mso-no-proof: yes;\">(Device Atlas, 2019)</span>.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: 150%;\"><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\">Ransomware:</span></strong><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\"> Ransomware can originate from a single device, and contaminate other connected devices <span style=\"mso-no-proof: yes;\">(Device Atlas, 2019)</span>.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: 150%;\"><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\">Keylogging:</span></strong><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\"> Some devices log keystrokes to capture usernames, passwords and any sensitive information that could be useful to a malicious criminal <span style=\"mso-no-proof: yes;\">(Device Atlas, 2019)</span>.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: 150%;\"><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\">Data Theft:</span></strong><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\"> The device can &ldquo;phones home&rdquo; and deliver stolen personal or business data to organized crime, or even state actors, in a manner hidden from the user <span style=\"mso-no-proof: yes;\">(Device Atlas, 2019)</span>.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: 150%;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\">Fake phones, batteries and chargers are made from cheap, substandard components and may contain chemicals that are dangerous to the environment and your health. The cheap and low-quality components used to manufacture fake phones and accessories are untested, uncertified and can be a safety hazard for users. The substandard components in fake phones often malfunction, with the potential to injure users and damage property. It&rsquo;s also believed fake phones are a drain on mobile phone networks, reducing network speed and reception for users (Obwot, 2019). </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: 150%;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\">So, we need to be aware of all the factors before purchasing not just mobile phones but also any technological item. It is very common in our country that whenever our relative, friends or peers recommend us to buy anything, we instantly believe and jump off to buy it. We are not heavily influenced by the so-called influencers scattered not just in Facebook but also in Tiktok, YouTube and other platforms. We can&rsquo;t control ourselves especially when we see discount offers. This shouldn&rsquo;t be the way. We cannot buy a technological item simply because it is on sale, or someone recommend it. We need to know what their sourcing is. Are they purchasing products from authentic supplier or from replica supplier like &lsquo;KK Concept&rsquo;? We have to analyze the comfortability, the authenticity, sustainability and also how much it is impacting our environment. We need to judge all these factors before buying a tech product. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: 150%;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\">So, now that we are aware of the counterfeit and original gadgets, we need to find out where can we get authentic product in Bangladesh where thousands of tech shops are opened with or without license, with or without surveillance. Not all of these sellers offer 100% original product. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: 150%;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\">Keeping all these factors in mind, a fully dedicated online e-commerce platform &lsquo;Tech Hut&rsquo; has been launched recently on 1<sup>st</sup> September 2021. It is an online based e-commerce platform that only sells 100% original, authentic, and licensed compact technological items. Tech Hut is fully dedicated in selling ultra-nano compact technological products and gadgets at a competitive market price. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: 150%;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\">In the present time, consumers prefer convenient products that are easy to use, operate and handy. At <span class=\"MsoHyperlink\"><a href=\"https://techhut.com.bd/shop\">techhut.com.bd</a></span>, you will find unique and authentic tech products that are very compact by nature which ultimately makes our lives convenient. The demand for such products has skyrocketed in this century and thus Tech Hut&rsquo;s mission is to sell compact, portable and convenient technological devices with inclusion of global brands to satisfy the growing need of exclusivity in Bangladesh market.</span></p>\r\n<h1 style=\"line-height: 150%;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 11.0pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\">References</span></strong></h1>\r\n<p class=\"MsoBibliography\" style=\"margin-left: .5in; text-indent: -.5in; line-height: 150%;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\"><span style=\"mso-no-proof: yes;\">Device Atlas. (2019, February 22). <em>Counterfeit smartphones and the threats they pose</em>. Retrieved from Device Atlas: https://deviceatlas.com/blog/counterfeit-smartphones-and-the-threats-they-pose</span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoBibliography\" style=\"margin-left: .5in; text-indent: -.5in; line-height: 150%;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif; mso-no-proof: yes;\">Obwot, S. (2019, September 10). <em>Dangers of using substandard or fake phones</em>. Retrieved from Tech Jaja: https://techjaja.com/dangers-of-using-substandard-fake-phones/</span></p>\r\n<p><!-- [if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n <o:OfficeDocumentSettings>\r\n  <o:AllowPNG/>\r\n </o:OfficeDocumentSettings>\r\n</xml><![endif]--><!-- [if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n <w:WordDocument>\r\n  <w:View>Normal</w:View>\r\n  <w:Zoom>0</w:Zoom>\r\n  <w:TrackMoves/>\r\n  <w:TrackFormatting/>\r\n  <w:PunctuationKerning/>\r\n  <w:ValidateAgainstSchemas/>\r\n  <w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>false</w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>\r\n  <w:IgnoreMixedContent>false</w:IgnoreMixedContent>\r\n  <w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>false</w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>\r\n  <w:DoNotPromoteQF/>\r\n  <w:LidThemeOther>EN-US</w:LidThemeOther>\r\n  <w:LidThemeAsian>X-NONE</w:LidThemeAsian>\r\n  <w:LidThemeComplexScript>BN</w:LidThemeComplexScript>\r\n  <w:Compatibility>\r\n   <w:BreakWrappedTables/>\r\n   <w:SnapToGridInCell/>\r\n   <w:WrapTextWithPunct/>\r\n   <w:UseAsianBreakRules/>\r\n   <w:DontGrowAutofit/>\r\n   <w:SplitPgBreakAndParaMark/>\r\n   <w:EnableOpenTypeKerning/>\r\n   <w:DontFlipMirrorIndents/>\r\n   <w:OverrideTableStyleHps/>\r\n  </w:Compatibility>\r\n  <m:mathPr>\r\n   <m:mathFo