(230, 'Apple Watch Series 6', '79362285', 'apple-watch-series-6', 'standard', 'C128', 191, 24, 1, 1, 1, '45000', '49999', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, '1623744106979876357.jpg', NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>The new top-end Apple Watch Series 6 is slightly faster, brighter and cheaper with a new sensor &ndash; and does just enough to stay the king of smartwatches. It also has a faster chip and a screen that is 2.5x brighter when in the &ldquo;always-on&rdquo; ambient mode, which is particularly noticeable outdoors. It comes in some new colours, including a blue or red aluminium. Our test watch, the aforementioned graphite-coloured stainless steel. Battery life is solid if not class leading. With the always-on display active and sleep tracking on overnight, the Series 6 lasts more than 36 hours between charges, lots of notifications and a 25-minute run. Sleep tracking overnight consumed between 10% and 12% of battery life, while a 25-minute outdoor run consumed about 4-5% of battery life. The Series 6 charges from flat to 100% in as little as 83 minutes and hits 80% in only 56 minutes using a 2A USB power adapter,</p>', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Model: Apple Series 6</p>\r\n<p>GPS Variant</p>\r\n<p>Music, Podcasts, and Audiobooks</p>\r\n<p>New sensor, New insights</p>\r\n<p>Display: 44mm (368 by 448 pixels) Retina LTPO OLED 1000 nits display</p>\r\n<p>Battery: Built-in rechargeable lithium-ion battery: Up to 18 hours<br />Magnetic charging cable</p>\r\n<p>Connectivity: Wi-Fi: 802.11b/g/n 2.4GHz and 5GHz<br />Bluetooth: v5.0</p>\r\n<p>SpecialFeatures: Water-resistant: 50 meters<br />Ambient light sensor</p>\r\n<p>Operating system: WatchOS 7</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 1, 0, 0, 0, '2021-06-15 18:01:46', '2021-09-18 08:48:58', NULL, NULL),
